SIMPLE: saxifrage
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saxifrage
<hw>Sax"i*frage</hw> <pr>(?; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>saxifraga</ets>, from <ets>saxifragus</ets> stone-breaking;
<ets>saxum</ets> rock + <ets>frangere</ets> to break: cf. F.
<ets>saxifrage</ets>. See <er>Fracture</er>, and cf. <er>Sassafras</er>,
<er>Saxon</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any plant of the genus
<gen>Saxifraga</gen>, mostly perennial herbs growing in crevices of
rocks in mountainous regions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Burnet saxifrage</b></col>, <cd>a European umbelliferous
plant (<spn>Pimpinella Saxifraga</spn>).</cd> -- <col><b>Golden
saxifrage</b></col>, <cd>a low half-succulent herb (<spn>Chrysosplenium
oppositifolium</spn>) growing in rivulets in Europe; also,
<spn>Chrysosplenium Americanum</spn>, common in the United States. See
also under <er>Golden</er>.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>Meadow
saxifrage</b></col>, or <col><b>Pepper saxifrage</b></col></mcol>.
<cd>See under <er>Meadow</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saxifragous</ent>⟦br⟧
